Project.0: STSP Cluster>Solar Terrestrial Science Programmes, Cluster

TEXT.0: The Wave of HIgh frequency and Sounder for Probing of Electron density

TEXT.1: by Relaxation (WHISPER) performs the measurement of the electron density

TEXT.2: on the four satellites of the CLUSTER project. The two main purposes of

TEXT.3: the WHISPER experiment are to record the natural waves and to make a

TEXT.4: diagnostic of the electron density using the sounding technique.

TEXT.5: The various working modes and the fourier transforms calculated on board

TEXT.6: provide a good frequency resolution obtained in the bandwidth 2-83 kHz.

TEXT.7: Onboard data compression by the Digital Wave Processing (DWP) intrument

TEXT.8: allows a good dynamic and level resolution of the electric signal amplitude.

MISSION_DESCRIPTION.0: The aim of the Cluster mission is to study small-scale structures of the magnetosphere

MISSION_DESCRIPTION.1: and its environment in three dimensions. To achieve this, Cluster is constituted of four

MISSION_DESCRIPTION.2: identical spacecraft that will flight in a tetrahedral configuration. The separation distances

MISSION_DESCRIPTION.3: between the spacecraft will be varied between ~3 km and 67 000 km, according to the

MISSION_REFERENCES.0: The Cluster and Phoenix Missions>Cluster project and instrument teams>Space Sci. Rev. 79, Nos. 1-2, 1997
